  "text": "PstI sites were added to both ends of the mGFP5 coding sequence [CITATION_1] ) using oligonucleotide primers. The GFP PstI fragment was inserted into the internal PstI site of a LFY cDNA in pAS116 [CITATION_2] , which contains a LFY cDNA with 300 bp of LFY 3′UTR and a nos terminator, creating pBS-GLFY. The GLFY/nos fragment was then ligated into the binary vector pMX202, X. Wu and others which includes the RBCS terminator sequence (M. A. Busch, personal communication) , along with the ML1 promoter fragment from pAS98 [CITATION_3] . ML1::GFP:LFY was created by ligating the ML1 promoter from pAS99 [CITATION_4] to the 5′ portion of GFP:LFY 5′ (up to the XbaI site in LFY) from pRTL2-sGFP:LFY, and the 3′ portion of LFY from pAS116 into binary vector pMX202. In this fusion, there is an additional serine inserted between GFP and LFY. 35S::GFP:LFY was created by ligating the same GFP:LFY 5′ and LFY 3′ fragments into binary vector pCHF3, which contains a CaMV 35S promoter [CITATION_5] .",
